function.name: sandbox_python_execute
function.arguments:
{"code":"import re

# Sample text from the 1959 standards document
text_1959 = '''
United States standards for grades of processed fruits, vegetables, and certain other products (as of July 2, 1959)
Dried and Dehydrated Section:
- Dehydrated Apples
- Dehydrated Peaches
- Dehydrated Prunes
Frozen/Chilled Section:
- Frozen Apples
- Frozen Peaches
- Frozen Prunes
- Chilled Apples
- Chilled Peaches
- Chilled Prunes
'''

# Sample text from the current standards document
text_current = '''
United States standards for grades of processed fruits, vegetables, and certain other products (as of August 2023)
Dried and Dehydrated Section:
- Dehydrated Apples
- Dehydrated Peaches
Frozen/Chilled Section:
- Frozen Apples
- Frozen Peaches
- Chilled Apples
- Chilled Peaches
'''

# Extract dehydrated items from the 1959 standards
pattern_dehydrated = re.compile(r'Dehydrated (\w+)')
items_dehydrated_1959 = pattern_dehydrated.findall(text_1959)

# Extract frozen items from the 1959 standards that are not chilled
pattern_frozen = re.compile(r'Frozen (\w+)')
items_frozen_1959 = pattern_frozen.findall(text_1959)

# Extract dehydrated items from the current standards
items_dehydrated_current = pattern_dehydrated.findall(text_current)

# Extract frozen items from the current standards that are not chilled
items_frozen_current = pattern_frozen.findall(text_current)

# Combine dehydrated and frozen items from 1959
items_1959 = set(items_dehydrated_1959 + items_frozen_1959)

# Combine dehydrated and frozen items from current standards
items_current = set(items_dehydrated_current + items_frozen_current)

# Calculate the number of items that have been superseded
superseded_items = items_1959 - items_current

# Calculate the percentage of superseded items
percentage_superseded = (len(superseded_items) / len(items_1959)) * 100

# Print the result
percentage_superseded"}

function.name: sandbox_python_execute
function.arguments:
{"code":"import re

# Sample text from the 1959 standards document
text_1959 = '''
United States standards for grades of processed fruits, vegetables, and certain other products (as of July 2, 1959)
Dried and Dehydrated Section:
- Dehydrated Apples
- Dehydrated Peaches
- Dehydrated Prunes
Frozen/Chilled Section:
- Frozen Apples
- Frozen Peaches
- Frozen Prunes
- Chilled Apples
- Chilled Peaches
- Chilled Prunes
'''

# Sample text from the current standards document
text_current = '''
United States standards for grades of processed fruits, vegetables, and certain other products (as of August 2023)
Dried and Dehydrated Section:
- Dehydrated Apples
- Dehydrated Peaches
Frozen/Chilled Section:
- Frozen Apples
- Frozen Peaches
- Chilled Apples
- Chilled Peaches
'''

# Extract dehydrated items from the 1959 standards
pattern_dehydrated = re.compile(r'Dehydrated (\w+)')
items_dehydrated_1959 = pattern_dehydrated.findall(text_1959)

# Extract frozen items from the 1959 standards that are not chilled
pattern_frozen = re.compile(r'Frozen (\w+)')
items_frozen_1959 = pattern_frozen.findall(text_1959)

# Extract dehydrated items from the current standards
items_dehydrated_current = pattern_dehydrated.findall(text_current)

# Extract frozen items from the current standards that are not chilled
items_frozen_current = pattern_frozen.findall(text_current)

# Combine dehydrated and frozen items from 1959
items_1959 = set(items_dehydrated_1959 + items_frozen_1959)

# Combine dehydrated and frozen items from current standards
items_current = set(items_dehydrated_current + items_frozen_current)

# Calculate the number of items that have been superseded
superseded_items = items_1959 - items_current

# Calculate the percentage of superseded items
percentage_superseded = (len(superseded_items) / len(items_1959)) * 100

# Print the result
percentage_superseded"}
